<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9815793985858></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9815793985858><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9815793985858>Good Question</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9815793985858#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2568><span id= >philoscope</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 7th 9:00 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Who would lead the band?<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;The question of whether there's any point to having more than one bard in a party is something I've frequently pondered.<br><br>  I find - to put it bluntly - that we bards have trouble not stepping on eachother's toes / stealing the lime-light.  I have not yet found songs that stack on themselves (i've heard that mana does, but I'm not there yet).  Maybe it's that I need more practice, but I'm so used to being the only bard, that I find it hard to think of six songs (sub 30) to sing....<br><br>  Though let me ponder in type....: Anthem, healing, rythym, Dennon's, psalm, Largo's....hmm, maybe....<br><br>  The one thing that I can't see (though I have seen this..."&lt;Me&gt;Hey &lt;name forgotten&gt; what you twisting?  &lt;name forgotten&gt;: Warsong.  &lt;Me&gt;: WHAT?") is Jonthan's.  Maybe someone can redeem this guy, I see Jonthan's to be greedy in a group, is there any rational that y'all can think of for using it (as opposed to any other song)?<br><br>  Even if there are enough songs to sing (which I now realize that there are), the time that it takes two to think of who will sing/play which songs is way too long.  In the time that the bards have finished squabling over territorial rights, the rest of the party has killed three or four mobs.  The thought of three bards in a party would give me an heart-attack.<br><br>Ehn-well....that's my rant for the day...good luck in the search for The Song.<br><br>Happy Trails<br>Philoscope<br>27th song<br>Terris-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br>Looking for love.....pity there's so little in humanity.</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
