<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98165847523387></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98165847523387><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98165847523387>RE: Good Question</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98165847523387#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 8th 6:58 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Philoscope,<br><br>I like your posts.<br><br>Additional songs might be Charm, Chains, Fear, Strike and some of the higher level songs even a 42nd bard needs to experience. As for stepping onto toes you can assign two important songs to each player and let them choose their own third song. Bards are so versatile that it seems there could be some creative things that could be done. If there were not enough songs to go arround you could use redundancy which would be a big help for resists and missed notes. A player could be assigned "like" instrument songs and juggle all three horn songs for instance Certainly we wouldn't have to "learn" the other team players abilities and that could be a big plus.<br><br>I have often appreciated having an extra bard in a group or for that matter an enchanter. I'm always grateful when someone else chains or snares the beasties so I can fear them non stop while I slash on their backsides. I would swap duties before there was a squable over who gets to sing the better songs... Still it would require some organization of resources.<br><br>Are there any higher level bards out there with comments?<br><br>Tinkle LilBelle<br>Bard of Brambledmoon.com<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
